c-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
c80  land use to stream routing
c 
c    defid       landuse default group id
c    deluid      land use id
c    route_suro  fraction of surface runoff that routes to the stream (0-1) (default=1)
c                if negative (<0) value then that fraction will be lost from the system
c    route_ifwo  fraction of interflow outflow that routes to the stream (0-1) (default=1)
c                if negative (<0) value then that fraction will be lost from the system
c    route_agwo  fraction of groundwater outflow that routes to the stream (0-1) (default=1)
c                if negative (<0) value then that fraction will be lost from the system
c 
c    Example: 0.3 means 30% of outflow routes to the stream and 70% bypasses to the next down stream in the reach network
c            -0.3 means 30% of outflow is permanently lost from the system and 70% routes to the stream
c             Enter a value of -1 to permanently lose all water from the respective layer
c             This convention applies to all three parameters (route_suro, route_ifwo, and route_agwo)
c 
c	defid	deluid	route_suro	route_ifwo	route_agwo
